{
  "document_id": "prov-22",
  "title": "Proverbs 22",
  "type": "study-bible",
  "translation": "Oxford",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-heading-23",
      "type": "heading",
      "text": "23"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "The rich and the poor have this in common: the Lord is the maker of them all."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-3",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "2 : See 14.31n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 2,
      "verse_end": 2
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "The clever see danger and hide; but the simple go on, and suffer for it."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-4",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "3 : See 27.12.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 3,
      "verse_end": 3
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "The reward for humility and fear of the Lord is riches and honor and life."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-6",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "4 : , see 1.7n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 4,
      "verse_end": 4
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "Thorns and snares are in the way of the perverse; the cautious will keep far from them."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-5",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "4–5 : See 10.2–3n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 4,
      "verse_end": 5
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Train children in the right way, and when old, they will not stray."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "The rich rule over the poor, and the borrower is the slave of the lender."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-7",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "7 : Economic disparities fuel disparities in power and position; see 6.1–5.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 7,
      "verse_end": 7
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "Whoever sows injustice will reap calamity, and the rod of anger will fail."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-8",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "8 : , a metaphor for acts and consequences (e.g., 1.31; 11.18).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 8,
      "verse_end": 8
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "Those who are generous are blessed, for they share their bread with the poor."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "Drive out a scoffer, and strife goes out; quarreling and abuse will cease."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-9",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "10 : , see 1.22n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 10,
      "verse_end": 10
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "Those who love a pure heart and are gracious in speech will have the king as a friend."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "The eyes of the Lord keep watch over knowledge, but he overthrows the words of the faithless."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-10",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "12 : , see 2.22n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 12,
      "verse_end": 12
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "The lazy person says, “There is a lion outside! I shall be killed in the streets!”"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-11",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "13 : No excuse is too absurd for ; see 26.13.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 13,
      "verse_end": 13
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "The mouth of a loose woman is a deep pit; he with whom the Lord is angry falls into it."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-12",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "14 : , i.e., “strange” woman, see 2.16n.; cf. 23.27.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 14,
      "verse_end": 14
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "Folly is bound up in the heart of a boy, but the rod of discipline drives it far away."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-13",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "15 : , see 10.13n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 15,
      "verse_end": 15
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "Oppressing the poor in order to enrich oneself, and giving to the rich, will lead only to loss."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-1",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "10.1–22.16: The proverbs of Solomon. Comprised predominantly of two-line proverbs, the oldest section of Proverbs can be divided into 10.1–15.33, which features antithetical proverbs, and 16.1–22.16, which includes a mix of proverbial forms.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 1,
      "verse_end": 16
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-14",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "16 : , perhaps as a gift or bribe, see 17.8n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 16,
      "verse_end": 16
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "The words of the wise: Incline your ear and hear my words, and apply your mind to my teaching;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "for it will be pleasant if you keep them within you, if all of them are ready on your lips."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "So that your trust may be in the Lord, I have made them known to you today—yes, to you."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "Have I not written for you thirty sayings of admonition and knowledge,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-17",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "20 : , the number of instructions contained in .",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 20,
      "verse_end": 20
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "to show you what is right and true, so that you may give a true answer to those who sent you?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-16",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "17–21 : Direct address and a call to attention recall chs 1–9; see 1.8–9n.; cf. 23.19.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 17,
      "verse_end": 21
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-18",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "21 : , i.e., be an honest and reliable messenger; see 13.17n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 21,
      "verse_end": 21
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Do not rob the poor because they are poor, or crush the afflicted at the gate;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "for the Lord pleads their cause and despoils of life those who despoil them."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-19",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "22–23 : , see 14.31n. , the site of the market and legal proceedings, see 1.20–21n.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 22,
      "verse_end": 23
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "Make no friends with those given to anger, and do not associate with hotheads,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "or you may learn their ways and entangle yourself in a snare."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-20",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "24–25 : Cautions about anger, see 12.16n. warns about the “heated man” or hothead.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 24,
      "verse_end": 25
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "Do not be one of those who give pledges, who become surety for debts."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "If you have nothing with which to pay, why should your bed be taken from under you?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-21",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "26–27 : , see 6.1–5n. The law stipulated that debtors’ cloaks had to be returned to them at night (e.g., Ex 22.25–26; Deut 24.12–13), but no provision existed for guarantors.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 26,
      "verse_end": 27
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "Do not remove the ancient landmark that your ancestors set up."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-22",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "28 : , see 15.25n.; cf. 23.10–11.",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 28,
      "verse_end": 28
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-29",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 29,
      "text": "Do you see those who are skillful in their work? They will serve kings; they will not serve common people."
    },
    {
      "block_id": "oxford-prov-22-h1kj-15",
      "type": "commentary",
      "text": "22.17–24.22: The words of the wise. An artful adaptation of the Egyptian ; see Introduction. Sages in the ancient Near East honed their thoughts on the wisdom literature of neighboring cultures (see 30.1–33; 31.1–9).",
      "canonical_ref": {
        "work": "bible",
        "book": "prov",
        "chapter": 22
      },
      "verse_start": 17,
      "verse_end": 29
    }
  ]
}